==English==

===Adjective===
'''asleep''' ([[predicative]] only)

# In a state of [[sleep]]; also, broadly, [[rest]]ing.  ''"I was asleep when you called."''
# {{tag|slang}} Inattentive.  ''"How could you miss that?  Were you asleep?"''
# {{tag|of a body part}} Having a [[numb]] or [[prickle|prickling]] sensation accompanied by a degree of [[unresponsiveness]].
#* '''2003:''' Norma L. Bronoski, ''Nuns Don't Dance''
#*: Louisa sat in the car crying, until her foot fell asleep. She shook her foot violently, afraid the numbness would turn to frostbite.

